==Tobacco industry in popular culture==

The tobacco industry has had a long relationship with the entertainment industry. In silent era movies, back-lit smoke was often used by filmmakers to create sense of mystery and sensuality in a scene. Later, cigarettes were deliberately placed in the hands of Hollywood stars as an early phase of [[product placement]],<ref>{{cite web|author=C Mekemson1, S A Glantz2 |url=http://tobaccocontrol.bmj.com/content/11/suppl_1/i81.full |title=How the tobacco industry built its relationship with Hollywood - Mekemson and Glantz 11 (suppl 1): i81 - Tobacco Control |publisher=Tobaccocontrol.bmj.com |date= |accessdate=2012-03-13}}</ref> until health regulating bodies tightened rules on tobacco advertisement and anti-smoking groups pressured actors and studio executives against such tactics. [[Big Tobacco]] has since been the subject focus of films such as the [[docudrama]] ''[[The Insider (film)|The Insider]]'' (1999) and ''[[Thank You for Smoking (film)|Thank You For Smoking]]'' (2005).

These issues have also constituted a recurring storyline in the [[AMC (TV channel)|AMC]] series ''[[Mad Men]]'', from [[Mad Men (season 1)|season 1]] beginning with the pilot episode ([[Smoke Gets in Your Eyes (Mad Men)|"Smoke Gets In Your Eyes"]]) through season 7's midseason finale, [[Mad Men (season 7)|"Waterloo"]]. In another television show, the [[Netflix]] original program [[List of Orange Is the New Black episodes#Season 2 .282014.29|''Orange Is the New Black'' season 2]], episode 2 ("Looks Blue, Tastes Red"), "[[List of characters from Orange Is the New Black#Inmates|Black Cindy]] bring[s] some [[Ralph Nader|Naderism]] to Lichtfield (a women's federal penitentiary) when talking about [[Altria Group|Philip Morris]]: 'Nah they ain't so bad. The people can decide for themselves if they wanna smoke. The real evil is them companies killing us without our consent. [[Monsanto]]. [[Rio Tinto Group|Rio Tinto]]. [[Big Pharma conspiracy theory|Big Pharma]]. [[British Petroleum|BP]]. [[Halliburton]]. I've been reading there's some dark shit goin' down. Not that those motherfuckers are ever gonna hire us! The real criminals? They don't bother with small timers.' ".<ref>{{cite news|work=The Atlantic| url= https://www.theatlantic.com/entertainment/archive/2014/06/the-orange-is-the-new-black-binge-review-episodes-1-through-6/372320/| date=June 2014| title= The ''Orange is the New Black'' Binge Review, Season 2: Episodes 1 through 6}}</ref>

